2 seed Duke took down top-seeded Georgia 8-5 and 8-4 in a doubleheader Monday at Foley Field to play its way all the way out of the loser's bracket and win the Athens Regional after dropping its first game.
"Pretty much every start, the day after, I asked Coach Pollard if I was going to be live that day," Stallings said, and it was hard to tell if he was joking.
Earlier in the afternoon, the Blue Devils forced the second game of the day with another comeback victory .
But that lead quickly evaporated when the Bulldogs struck for four runs in the second inning.
Sophomore Graeme Stinson replaced Bill Chillari with one out in the second inning and shut Georgia down through the end of the sixth, only allowing one more run and tallying eight strikeouts.